'''Niko Kristian Sigur''' (born September 9, 2003) is a Canadian professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] or [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[Croatian Football League|HNL]] club [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] and the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/tko-je-niko-sigur-19-hajdukov-debitant-kad-mi-je-leko-rekao-da-cu-igrati-bio-sam-nervozan-905884|first=Josip|last=Tolić|title=Tko je Niko Sigur (19), Hajdukov debitant? 'Kad mi je Leko rekao da ću igrati, bio sam nervozan'|newspaper=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]]|publisher=[[Styria Media Group]]|date=April 23, 2023|access-date=March 24, 2025|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/hnl/klubovi/hajduk/evo-tko-je-sljedeci-na-redu-za-prikljucivanje-prvoj-momcadi-hajduka-on-vec-sada-radi-razliku-na-terenu-15329663|first=Dražen|last=Krušelj|title=Evo Tko Je Sljedeći Na Redu Za Priključivanje Prvoj Momčadi Hajduka, On Već Sada Radi Razliku Na Terenu|website=jutarnji.hr|date=April 26, 2023|access-date=March 24, 2025|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nogomania.rs/Vest/Magican-put-za-365-dana-Niko-Sigur-od-ulicnog-fudbalera-do-debija-za-prvi-tim-Hajduka|first=Miloš|last=Zekić|title=Magičan put za 365 dana: Niko Sigur, od uličnog fudbalera do debija za prvi tim Hajduka|website=Nogomania|date=April 23, 2023|access-date=March 24, 2025|language=hr}}</ref>

==Early life==
Sigur was born in [[Burnaby]], [[British Columbia]], and first began playing soccer with Mountain United FC in [[Burnaby]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Alumni Players|url=https://mufc.ca/alumni-players|url-status=dead|website=Mountain United FC|access-date=April 23, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423150835/https://mufc.ca/alumni-players|archive-date=April 23, 2023}}</ref> in which he won the 2016 BC provincial championship and the 2018 BCSPL League Cup title.<ref name="auto"/> He was then selected to play for the [[Whitecaps FC Academy]], winning the USSDA Northwest Division championship in 2018. He attended at [[Notre Dame Regional Secondary School]] at the high school level, where he won the 2019 BC AA provincial championship.<ref name="auto"/>

==University career==
Sigur played one year of [[College soccer in the United States|university soccer]] at [[York University]] in 2021. During his university career, he started in 10 of 11 matches, scoring two goals and registering one assist. He was named York's athlete of the week in November for his semifinal play-off performance, which saw him score the winning goal against [[Ryerson University|Ryerson]] in the 119th minute and recording an assist in the same game. York would later finish with a silver medal the [[Ontario University Athletics|OUA]] championship during his only season.<ref name="auto"/>

==Club career==
===Academy===
Sigur played for [[Vaughan Azzurri]]'s "C" team in 2021, making two appearances for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Niko Sigur|url=https://www.league1ontario.com/roster_players/49523063|url-status=dead|website=League1 Ontario|access-date=April 23, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423150833/https://league1ontario.com/roster_players/49523063|archive-date=April 23, 2023}}</ref> Sigur moved to [[Slovenia]] in early 2022, joining [[NK Radomlje|Radomlje]] youth team.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Niko Sigur NK Radomlje NK Brinje Grosuplje|url=https://www.nk-radomlje.si/kadeti-in-mladinci-povisali-prednost-pred-triglavom/niko-sigur-nk-radomlje-nk-brinje-grosuplje/|website=NK Radomlje|date=May 16, 2022|access-date=April 23, 2023|language=hr}}</ref>

===Hajduk Split===
In 2022, Sigur transferred to [[HNK Hajduk Split Reserves and Academy|Hajduk Split]] in [[Croatia]] to play for their academy, registering two goals and three assists in his first youth season.<ref name="auto2">{{Cite web|title=Za Hajduk debitirao igrač koji je prošle godine igrao na ulici|url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/za-hajduk-debitirao-igrac-koji-je-prosle-godine-igrao-na-ulici/2457387.aspx|website=Index Sport|date=April 23, 2023|access-date=March 24, 2025|language=hr}}</ref> He was ineligible to play in [[HNK Hajduk Split Reserves and Academy|Hajduk Split]]'s historic [[2022-23 UEFA Youth League|UEFA Youth League]] run due to a special rule where older players in the junior ages must have at least two years of club experience in order to be eligible to play.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Slaven|last=Alfirević|title=Tko je neočekivani debitant u momčadi Hajduka? Junior koji ne smije nastupati u Europi zbog posebnog pravila|url=https://slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/hajduk/tko-je-neocekivani-debitant-u-momcadi-hajduka-junior-koji-ne-smije-nastupati-u-europi-zbog-posebnog-pravila-1283507|newspaper=[[Slobodna Dalmacija]]|publisher=[[Hanza Media]]|date=April 22, 2023|access-date=April 23, 2023|language=hr}}</ref>

Due to injuries of [[Dino Mikanović]] and [[Gergő Lovrencsics]], Sigur made his official senior debut as a [[right back]] in a 2–0 victory against [[NK Varaždin (2012)|Varaždin]] on April 22, 2023.<ref name="auto1">{{cite web|title=Niko Sigur: Bio sam nervozan prije debija, ali suigrači su mi puno pomogli|url=https://hajduk.hr/vijest/niko-sigur-bio-sam-nervozan-prije-debija-ali-suigraci-su-mi-puno-pomogli/15815|website=HNK Hajduk Split|access-date=April 23, 2023|language=hr}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Hajduk Split against Varaždin on February 24, 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dosad u karijeri nije zabio gol, a onda je golčinom spasio Hajduk|url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/pogledajte-golcinu-sigura-kojom-je-spasio-hajduk-poraza/2541587.aspx|website=Index Sport|date=February 24, 2024|access-date=March 24, 2025|language=hr}}</ref>

==International career==
Sigur holds dual citizenship of Canada and Croatia.<ref name="dilemma">{{Cite web|url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/dual-citizenship-dilemma-talented-niko-sigur-chooses-croatia/|title=Dual Citizenship Dilemma: Talented Niko Sigur chooses Croatia|website=Croatia Week|date=May 30, 2023|access-date=23 March 2025}}</ref> In 2023, he received call-ups to the [[Croatia national under-21 football team|Croatia U21]] ahead of the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] and the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canadian national team]], and opted to represent the former.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/mlada-zvijezda-hajduka-prelomila-izmedju-kanade-i-hrvatske-mnoge-ce-iznenaditi-njegova-odluka---784037.html|title=Mlada zvijezda Hajduka prelomila između Kanade i Hrvatske?|website=Gol.hr|date=May 27, 2023|access-date=March 23, 2025|language=hr}}</ref><ref name="dilemma"/>

In May 2024, Sigur was named as a standby player for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia senior national team]] ahead of [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Croatia head coach Dalić presents preliminary EURO 2024 squad |url=https://hns.team/en/news/27852/croatia-head-coach-dalic-presents-preliminary-euro-2024-squad/#:~:text=Stand-by:%20Borna%20Bari%C5%A1i%C4%87%20(,,%20Petar%20Su%C4%8Di%C4%87%20(Dinamo). |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=hns.team |language=en}}</ref>

In August 2024, the [[Croatian Football Federation]] announced that Sigur had decided to switch his international allegiance and would be representing Canada.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sigur odlučio promijeniti nogometno državljanstvo|url=https://hns.team/vijesti/28196/sigur-odlucio-promijeniti-nogometno-drzavljanstvo/|publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]]|date=August 22, 2024|access-date=March 23, 2025|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5712845/2024/08/21/canada-croatia-niko-sigur-switch/|title=Croatia dual national Niko Sigur switches to Canada|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first=Joshua|last=Kloke|date=August 22, 2024|via=The Athletic}}</ref> On August 27, he was officially called up by Canada for two friendly matches against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] and [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/niko-sigur-canada-roster-friendlies-september-1.7306021|date=August 27, 2024|title=Midfielder Niko Sigur, winger Stephen Afrifa added to Canada roster for September friendlies|first=Daniel|last=Rainbird|website=[[CBC Sports]]|access-date=March 23, 2025}}</ref> Sigur made his debut in a goalless friendly draw against the latter opponent on September 10.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Canada's Niko Sigur reflects on his debut against Mexico: "An incredible feeling"|url=https://en.nogomania.com/read/Canadas-Niko-Sigur-reflects-on-his-debut-against-Mexico-An-incredible-feeling|website=Nogomania|date=September 11, 2024|access-date=March 23, 2025}}</ref>

In June 2025, Sigur was named to the squad for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/canmnt-squad-announced-for-2025-concacaf-gold-cup/#:~:text=Defenders%20selected%20are%3A%20Sam%20Adekugbe,Niko%20Sigur%20from%20Hadjuk%20Split%2C|date=June 5, 2025|title=CANMNT squad announced for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup}}</ref> On June 17 in Canada's opening game against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]], he would score his first international goal in a 6-0 victory at [[BC Place]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/tani-time-oluwaseyi-leads-canada-past-honduras-in-gold-cup-opener|title=Tani time! Oluwaseyi leads Canada past Honduras in Gold Cup opener|date=June 18, 2025}}</ref> He was named to the Gold Cup Group Stage Best XI after scoring his first goal and recording an assist during the group stage.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-26 |title=Navas, Buchanan, Díaz headline Gold Cup Group Stage Best XI |url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/gold-cup/news/navas-buchanan-diaz-headline-gold-cup-group-stage-best-xi/ |access-date=2025-07-25 |website=Gold Cup |language=en}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Sigur is described as a very technical [[midfielder]] who can impact the game on both ends.<ref name="auto"/> He regards himself as a [[defensive midfielder]] who can also play in several midfield positions.<ref name="auto2"/> Sigur also plays as [[right back]], as shown on his senior professional debut.<ref name="auto1"/>

